This paper proposes a machine learning technique for classification tasks, specifically for imbalanced data classification. It discusses the limitations of conventional DBN and proposes a cost-sensitive approach to assign different misclassification costs for different classes. The paper also uses adaptive differential evolution optimization as the optimization algorithm. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of deep belief networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with imbalanced data classification, which is a sub-topic of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
